      "lesson title": "AI Feature Creep in Software Products",
      "order": 1,
      "Description": "In this lesson, you will explore how the rush to add artificial intelligence features to software products can quietly introduce unexpected risks and technical complexity. Many teams add AI capabilities without fully considering the design implications, and this often leads to bloated products that are harder to maintain, test, and explain to users. We will look at real-world patterns where well-intentioned AI additions have created confusion, eroded user trust, or made systems more fragile than before. By the end of this lesson, you will have a clearer understanding of what AI feature creep looks like in practice and why a thoughtful, design-led approach is essential before adding any AI capability to a product.",
