          "slidetitle": "Reducing AI Feature Creep Risk",
          "subtitle": "Strategies to keep AI additions focused.",
          "slidecontent": "• Define a clear problem before adding any AI feature\n• Tie each AI addition to a specific, measurable user need\n• Short feedback loops catch scope drift early\n• Review AI features regularly against original goals\n• Kill features that add complexity without clear benefit\n• Involve non-technical stakeholders in scoping decisions"
        },
        {
          "number": 8,
          "slidetitle": "What to Remember",
          "subtitle": "Core lessons to carry forward",
          "slidecontent": "• Every AI feature added without clear purpose increases complexity and risk\n• Users notice when AI feels bolted on\n• Start small, validate, then expand\n• Good AI design solves a real problem the user already has\n• Involve your team early, before the feature is built, not after\n• Review your existing product before adding anything new"
